{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17520641","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17520641"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T14:27:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T14:27:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13247"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"13247","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/13247"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.12,0.11,0.61,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5796"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107234"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5796","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5796"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13247"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89689"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"33"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"98"},{"type":"tags","id":"677"},{"type":"tags","id":"1287"},{"type":"tags","id":"2589"},{"type":"tags","id":"2602"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"5002"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"13206"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35945"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35974"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42871"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44910"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107234","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107234"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 60-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for a routine health check. She currently enjoys good health. Her medical history includes hypertension, for which she takes perindopril. She does not take any other regular medications. She does not smoke and drinks two glasses of wine at weekends. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. A systolic ejection murmur is evident. The rest of the examination is unremarkable.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA transthoracic echocardiogram reveals a bicuspid aortic valve and a dilated ascending aorta. A CT aortogram shows that the ascending aorta is 5.7 cm in diameter.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate plan of management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Repeat CT aortogram in six months","Add propranolol and review in three months","Repeat echocardiogram in six months","Surgical repair","Add verapamil and review in three months"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has been found to have a bicuspid aortic valve with significant dilatation of the ascending aorta (5.7 cm). The normal range of the diameter of the ascending aorta is 3 - 4 cm. The most appropriate management in this case is \u003Cstrong\u003Esurgical repair\u003C/strong\u003E. Current guidelines recommend that in asymptomatic patients with aneurysms of the aortic root or ascending aorta who have a maximum diameter of \u22655.5cm, surgery is indicated due to the increased risk of aortic dissection or rupture.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERepeating the CT scan in six months\u003C/strong\u003E would be inappropriate as the aortic diameter has already reached a size that warrants intervention. Delaying treatment could put the patient at unnecessary risk of aortic complications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdding propranolol\u003C/strong\u003E or other beta-blockers may be considered in patients with smaller aortic diameters to potentially slow the rate of aortic expansion. However, at this size, medical management alone is insufficient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERepeating the echocardiogram in six months\u003C/strong\u003E would also be inappropriate for the same reasons as delaying with a CT scan. The diagnosis is clear, and the aortic size warrants immediate action rather than further monitoring.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdding verapamil\u003C/strong\u003E, a calcium channel blocker, would not be the appropriate management for aortic dilatation. While it can be used in the management of hypertension, it is not specifically indicated for aortic dilatation management.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027s important to note that bicuspid aortic valve is associated with an increased risk of aortic dilatation and dissection compared to the general population. This patient\u0027s significant aortic dilatation, in combination with her bicuspid aortic valve, necessitates prompt surgical intervention to prevent potentially life-threatening complications such as aortic dissection or rupture. Following surgical repair, the patient will require lifelong surveillance with regular imaging to monitor for any recurrent dilatation or other aortic complications.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Surgical repair is indicated for bicuspid aortic valve with ascending aortic dilatation \u003E5.5 cm.","Bicuspid aortic valve is associated with an increased risk of aortic dilatation and dissection.","Regular imaging surveillance is crucial for patients with bicuspid aortic valve to monitor for aortic dilatation."],"references":["Isselbacher EM, Preventza O, Black JH, Augoustides JG, Beck AW, Bolen MA, et al. 2022 ACC/AHA guideline for the diagnosis and management of aortic disease: A report of the american heart association/American college of cardiology joint committee on clinical practice guidelines. Circulation. 2022 Nov 2;146(24). Available at: https://www.ahajournals.org/doi/10.1161/CIR.0000000000001106"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89689"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13247"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89689","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89689"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-26T17:20:29+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-26T17:20:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5796"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107234"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"33","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/33"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiothoracic Surgery","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,